    'date' => 'Mon, 31 Oct 1994 15:27:16  0600',
    'body' => 'More on the _Azhanti_/_Maggart_ horde fight:

I realized that the _Azhanti_ is missing one other major component 
that we\'d normally expect to see -- the 20% flicker "Vlandian" Black 
Globe.  I suppose that it was omitted to see how a conventional 
cruiser held up against a determined attack.  The high-performance 
jump drives in the _Azhanti_ make it ideal for a BG.  According to
FF&S, using the jump capacitors only, the TL14 _Azhanti_ drive can 
absorb up to 441000 MJ of incoming power before overloading.  But 
it doesn\'t say anywhere how to convert this into damage value, so 
this can\'t be easily converted to _Battle Rider_ damage points.

We have data for the _Kinunir_.  It can handle BR damage points
of 10, or 500-749 BL damage points.  The TL15 _Kinunir_ can take
at least 8750 MJ in its\' jump capacitors.  This suggests that 

  BL damage points == 5 * (square root of capacity in MJ)
  
in a similar manner to the formulae for the PAWS and Meson weapon
sequences in FF&S.  The _Kinunir_ doesn\'t quite fit this on jump 
capacitor capacity alone, but it would be reasonable if even a
miniscule auxiliary HPG bank were also installed in the ship.  (In
the single cubic meter range!)  Unfortunately, other potential
solutions are possible, so this is only a guess.

If this *is* accurate, then the BG-equipped _Azhanti_ would have an
incredible minimum HPG capacity of 18 _Battle Rider_ damage points, 
without an auxiliary HPG bank.

  Steve Bonneville
  <bonn0015@gold.tc.umn.edu>

