    'from' => 'rancke@diku.dk',
    'body' => 'Joni M Virolainen asks:
>Is it possible that when chirpers get offsprings and those offsprings go to
>that ritual in which the cast is chosen, they could become Droyne? Or is it
>that once chirper allway chirper?

Chirpers that dosen\'t get casted at puberty remains chirpers forever. I
originally thought that a chirper was just an unlucky droyne, and that
the offspring of any chirper could be casted if caught young enough. The
Old Traveller module _Alien Realms_ imply that it\'s more complicated than 
that. Apparently there are two different types of chirpers: chirpers who
has lost the knowledge to caste, but can be casted if there is a drone
with a set of coyns around, and chirpers who have lost the ability to
