Alvin Plummer writes:

> And: is anyone playing a TNE campagin set in the Trojan Rift

Sort of. The Alliance is most active in the Trojan Reach, but I won\'t be
using the standard TNE universe (Virus, etc.).

Les Howie writes:

>  If we say that the danger zone for a warship is within the 1 MJ/cm^2
sphere 

Okay, that sounds more reasonable. The next question is: what does 1MJ/cm^2
mean in terms of High Guard damage?

Derek Smith writes:

> And while we\'re at this, OK, KEN, WHY DON\'T YOUR ALLIANCE SHIPS
> HAVE MESON SCREENS?

Following the Cluster Liberation War, the Alliance Navy looked at adding
meson screens to its warships, but decided that they weren\'t worth the
(considerable) energy expenditure. The big meson guns that the Alliance was
most worried about would only be stopped by meson screens around 1/6 of the
time, so the Alliance decided instead to rely on high agility and long-range
weapons. Also, meson screens block meson communications, and the Alliance was
more interested in secure communications than slightly improved defenses.
When AM ships (with effectively unlimited power available) came along, meson
screens were omitted because the Navy had gotten along okay without them so
far. 

Some officers in the Alliance Navy have argued that the usefullness of
agility and better range as a replacement for meson screens is overrated, but
to date Alliance warships have gotten along without them.

Ken
