Well, it\'s still vulnerable to meson gun attack, and if it has a meson
screen active, it can\'t fire, which is exactly what the invader wants.
One would think one could use triangulation-type techniques to locate
it based on its firing patterns. Human intelligence is also useful -
let those spooks in Naval Intelligence earn their paychecks! Find
someone in the Department of Planetary Defense who has a debt problem
or something.

>The buried meson gun will need sensors on the surface to see enemy
>ships so it can shoot them.

Not only on the surface of the planet - off the planet as well, if the
