    'body' => '
There have been complaints on tml about the penetration performance of 
(small arms) lasers.
The rules in FF&S have made the assumption that it is impossible to focus a 
laser on any area with a diameter smaller than 1 cm!
As this is clearly at variance with reality I propose a new rule.

Lasers may be designed with a short range less than the maximum allowed.
This may result in an intensity (I) greater than that at the maximum 
allowed. This intensity (I) figure is to be used for IPR calculations ONLY.
The normal intensity figure is used for damage calculations.

This should make handheld (but short ranged) lasers more capable against 
armoured targets.

Django.
