    'topic' => 'comments on deep Site Meson Guns',
    'body' => 'Lots of people responded to my initial post, so I\'ll just respond to them in
bulk.  

Several people suggested either nuking the entire planet, or dropping
rocks on it.  I was trying to avoid destroying the planet, and
commiting genocide.  Also I think according to the old Library Data
book, didn\'t the imperial rules of War prohibit the use of nuclear weapons.  

Another popular idea, is treason.  While this is the ideal situation,
knowing where the gun is before hand, I didn\'t think it would always be
possible, otherwise why have a deep site gun.  Though i am sure
considerable effort would be directed down this road.  

Erich Schneider says:
>One would think one could use triangulation-type techniques to locate
>it based on its firing patterns.
I can\'t see how. The only way to detect the mesons is to be a target,
and  the target probably won\'t be long for this world.  Meson guns are
firing rather tight beams of particles, triangulation normally works
for broadcasting, like Tv or radio signals.  

>Not only on the surface of the planet - off the planet as well, if the
>sensors have meson communicators installed.

Why would they need sensors off the planet?  I hadn\'t really thought
about how the sensors communicate with the gun, if they used local
phone lines or something, these would just become the target, so they
would need meson communicators.  But those are really expensive, and
only available at TL 15, i think, Maybe they could have dedicated
lines, buried underground, or something, still pretty expensive.
Something to think about.


 StarWolf says:
> 2. Detonate several nukes in the upper atmosphere. This will destroy 
> most electronic hardware. And sensors are very hard to shield against 
> these types of attack. Their antennas have to be disconnected 
> *before* the Electromagnetic Pulse arrive. Circuit breakers may 
> protect the process units against EMP, but the antennas will most 
> likely be fried.

I kind of assume by tl 15 electronics can be hardened pretty easily,
and cheaply.  Isn\'t this normally done with by encasing all electronics in
metal, 

Andy Lilly says:
>MISSILES
>Just direct ARMs (Anti-Radiation Missiles) or a higher tech equivalent at
>the planet\'s surface. If the missiles are tuned to the frequencies used by
>the meson gun\'s sensors then you won\'t go hitting every single military
>sensor, just the important ones. You\'d still need an excess of missiles (vs.
>number of sensors) to allow for anti-missile laser defences, etc. but it
>ought to work.

The planet would be using passive sensors.  With the diameter of a
planet to work with, you can have a pretty good passive sensor.  

>JAMMING
>Jam the meson gun sensors from a starship (probably disguised as a merchant
>ship) or, better still, from one or more covert teams operating on the
>ground (requires far less power than from space because the jammers are so
>much closer to the sensors)
This would only slow down the gun.  

ZSABOTAGE
>Destroy selected sensor sites using covert ground teams. Perhaps they might
>even gain access to the meson gun site?
>SABOTAGE 2
>Gain access to any one sensor site using a covert team - try not to let
>anyone else know you\'ve got in. Implant a virus (not \'The Virus\') in their
>software - preferably in the communications section; watch as all
>communications between the gun and the sensors are cut off at a
>predetermined time (just before your ships get in range). Attack!

This was the best that I could come up with also.  As someone else
pointed out, it does make for a dandy adventure idea.

>LOSE POWER
>The meson gun must require a substantial power plant with a fuel system. By
>the use of covert ground operatives, either (a) contaminate the fuel, (b)
>disable the power plant by infiltrating the engineering staff, sending a
>sabotage robot down an airshaft, drop a nuke down an airshaft, direct a
>nuclear damper at the power plant, etc., etc.

I figured the power plant is next to the gun, ie deep underground also.
 the fuel would just be hydrogen, so kinda of hard to contaminate.  The
best way to get the hydrogen would be from an  undeground river, and
just purify it on the premises.  

 Cynthia says:
>#1: Put heavy meson screens on your assault landers and 
>assault cruisers.
Tariq, had actually designed this thing to blow through heavy meson
screens.  He said he will post it soon, probably after finals are done
with this week.  That is also really expensive, but then again so is
this meson gun. :)

>Yep.  Why do you think Hi-tech, Hi-Pop Imperial worlds are
>nearly impossible to invade?
I guess this is why Lucan started the Black War.  
Does anyone remeber what TL Terra was at, when it was captured. 
Wondering if it had any meson guns. That assualt took along time, if I
remember correctly, can\'t remember the source though.  Anyone have a better
memory.

Lewis
