    'body' => 'Hey all:

A few years ago (maybe 10, I dunno\') I developed a rather extensive
database of information as well as a bunch of new ships for the
original GDW Traveller.

One in particular was based on the current ballistic missile
submarines.  A stealthed cruiser carrying 18 or so 50 ton, Durasteel
slugs, with ablative reentry coatings.  This thing pops in-system,
somewhere over the plane of the ecliptic and a good distance out from
the target planet, and pumps these puppies out at 25,000 Kps.  The
onboard computers are large enough to compute orbital tracks for impact
on population centers (there\'s no real need to be accurate or
anything).  The ship itself dumps back into warp, and is gone.  A month
later, if all goes properly (and it should, finding 50 tons of radar
absorbing material outside of the normal plane of search has got to be
exceedingly difficult), You should be able to PULVERIZE any pretargeted
sites dirt-side.  It makes for a nice, clean (radiation-wise), softener
for assault troops.  Hell, if the planet is small enough, you might
just peel off the atmospheric shell.

As a matter of fact, this would make one hell of a blackmail tool. 
Hold whole planets under the "Rocks of Damocles" as it were.  They pay,
you pipe them the orbital tracks.  The don\'t pay, POOF, instant
ice-age.  Oh what a drag, sucks to be you.

- Jim Dethlefsen
  Systems Engineer (and destroyer of civilizations)
  Electronic Data Systems, Inc.
  OSD Backbone Services
