Howdy,

well, I got another mini (the free trader) and thought I\'d make a couple
comments.  

The sculpt is pretty good (though the mold had some rips that I could see).
I\'ve always liked the Beowolf design, and it is pretty true to it.  The turrets
come as two additional pieces.  The only real problems are related to the 
casting job, which isn\'t as good as the PC (I cast stuff for a living, so I\'m
a bit hyper-sensitive to this, I guess :)

My recurrent question is:  What scale is it in?  I know from Loren\'s post
that
they are not all in the same scale, but it would be nice to at least have the

scale printed on the package so my players won\'t ask "so how much bigger
would
the Patrol Cruiser really be?"

If I knew what alloy they were using getting the volume would be easy, but I
don\'t.  I\'m recasting it in a known resin to calculate the volume... I\'ll
post 
the scale when I get it done. (I know I could displace water to do the same,
but
I\'d rather have an extra to make into a wreak :)

BTW, does anyone have deck plans for the PC?  What is the length on it really
supposed to be?

-Merrick
